@endnode

@node Installation "How to intall this package"

                        How to intall this package

  To  install  this  package simply copy the executables Login, Logout, su,
chmod, chown and chgrp to C:

  If  you  aren't  using  Kickstart  V39+  (3.0 or greater) you should copy
chown37/chgrp37 instead of chown/chgrp and rename those to chown/chgrp.

  Finally if the pure bit isn't set for the files you should set it:
	chmod +p C:Login C:Logout C:su C:chmod C:chown C:chgrp
don't  worry  that chmod doesn't print out any text here, it's a clone of a
UNIX  command  and  as such it's very quiet, but if something goes wrong it
will let you know.
@endnode

@node Bugs "Known Bugs"

                                 Know Bugs

  There  are no known bugs in this distribution, but there is however a bug
in  multiuser.library  that causes the computer to crash if you use the OWN
switch  in  Login.  If  this  bug  is  a  problem  please  take  a  look at
Aminet:util/misc/MultiUserFix.lha.

  If you find anything else please @{"contact me" Link Author}.
@endnode

